# Keep host build artefacts out of the Docker build context.
#
# Without this, `COPY frontend/packages/ ...` in Dockerfile.frontend copies the
# host's node_modules — a pnpm symlink farm pointing into the host store — over
# the tree installed inside the image, breaking module resolution. CI never hit
# this because a fresh checkout has no node_modules; local builds always did.

# Dependencies (reinstalled inside the image)
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Build outputs
#
# NOTE: do NOT exclude build/ — Dockerfile.service copies the Spring fat JAR
# from services/<service>/build/libs/, so excluding it breaks every backend
# image build. The context-size win here comes from node_modules, not build/.
.next
**/.next
dist
**/dist
out
**/out

# VCS and tooling
.git
.gitignore
.github
.idea
.vscode
.remember
.claude

# Local env and secrets — must never enter an image layer
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Read-only template reference (see CLAUDE.md); never shipped
template

# Misc
*.log
.DS_Store
coverage
**/coverage
